From
\href{Science:Math_Exam_Resources/Courses/MATH152/April_2010/Question_B1_(a)}{B1(a)}
we have that

\begin{align*}
A=\begin{bmatrix}
1  &  -2  &  0\\
8  &  0  &  8\\
16  &  16  &  16
\end{bmatrix}\end{align*}

and

\begin{align*}
\mathbf{b}=\begin{bmatrix}
0\\
6\\
14
\end{bmatrix}.\end{align*}

The augmented matrix for $A\mathbf{x}=\mathbf{b}$ is $[A|\mathbf{b}]$.
This says to take the matrix $A$ and add the vector $\mathbf{b}$ as an
extra column. Therefore the augmented matrix is

\begin{align*}
\left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
1  &  -2  &  0 & 0\\
8  &  0  &  8 & 6\\
16  &  16  &  16 & 14
\end{array}\right]\end{align*}
